   na putanji: /home/student/exam-shortcut.


TASK 2 — User, Group, and Password Policy  (20 pts, ~15 min)
Korisnici, grupe i politika lozinki
--------------------------------------------------------------
You are provisioning accounts for a new team of database administrators.
Postavljate korisničke račune za novi tim administratora baze podataka.

NOTE / NAPOMENA: The dbteam group already exists on your system — do not
delete and recreate it, just confirm the GID matches and proceed.
Grupa dbteam već postoji na vašem sustavu — nemojte je brisati i ponovno
stvarati, samo potvrdite da se GID podudara i nastavite.

1. Create a group named dbteam with GID {{ exam_gid }}.  (3 pts)
   Stvorite grupu dbteam s GID-om {{ exam_gid }}.

2. Create a user named {{ exam_username }} with:  (2+2+3 pts)
   Stvorite korisnika {{ exam_username }} s:
   - dbteam as a supplementary group / dbteam kao dodatnom grupom
   - Initial password: Welcome1 / Početna lozinka: Welcome1
   - Password must be changed on first login / Lozinka mora biti promijenjena pri prvoj prijavi

3. Set the following password policy for {{ exam_username }}:  (6 pts — 2 each)
   Postavite sljedeću politiku lozinke za {{ exam_username }}:
   - Minimum days between password changes: 7
     Minimalan broj dana između promjena lozinke: 7
   - Maximum days before password change is required: 60
     Maksimalan broj dana do obvezne promjene lozinke: 60
   - Account expiry date: {{ exam_expiry }}
     Datum isteka računa: {{ exam_expiry }}

4. Allow {{ exam_username }} to run any command with sudo without a password
   prompt. Use a dedicated file in /etc/sudoers.d/.  (4 pts)
   Dopustite korisniku {{ exam_username }} izvršavanje bilo koje naredbe putem
   sudo bez unosa lozinke. Koristite zasebnu datoteku u /etc/sudoers.d/.


TASK 3 — File Permissions and Collaborative Directory  (20 pts, ~15 min)
Dozvole datoteka i zajednički direktorij
-------------------------------------------------------------------------
The dbteam group needs a shared workspace where all members can create and
modify files, but cannot delete each other's work.
Grupi dbteam potreban je zajednički radni prostor u kojemu svi članovi mogu
stvarati i mijenjati datoteke, ali ne mogu brisati tuđe datoteke.

1. Create the directory /home/{{ exam_workspace }}.  (2 pts)
   Stvorite direktorij /home/{{ exam_workspace }}.

2. Set the group owner to dbteam.  (3 pts)
   Postavite vlasnika grupe na dbteam.

3. Set permissions so that:  (1+2+2 pts)
   Postavite dozvole tako da:
   - Owner has full read, write, and execute access
     Vlasnik ima puna prava čitanja, pisanja i izvršavanja
   - Group members have read, write, and execute access
     Članovi grupe imaju prava čitanja, pisanja i izvršavanja
   - All other users have no access
     Svi ostali korisnici nemaju nikakav pristup

4. Set the SGID bit on the directory.  (4 pts)
   Postavite SGID bit na direktorij.

5. Set the sticky bit on the directory.  (4 pts)
   Postavite sticky bit na direktorij.

6. Configure {{ exam_username }}'s shell so that umask is persistently
   set to 007.  (2 pts)
   Konfigurirajte ljusku (shell) korisnika {{ exam_username }} tako da umask
   bude trajno postavljen na 007.

Expected final permissions / Očekivane konačne dozvole: drwxrws--T


